The paper discusses a new machine learning model, the Convolutional Tsetlin Machine, which is an alternative to convolutional neural networks. The paper focuses on pattern recognition tasks and proposes a model that is both interpretable and hardware-near. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the model, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
